cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new architecture for gated recurrent neural networks that improves their performance in analyzing sequential data. It also involves the use of adaptable parameters and experiments on a dataset. Other likely sub-categories include cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves the use of neural networks, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as it uses the MNIST dataset, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the development of a new architecture for neural networks, and cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it involves the analysis of sequential data.
